wikipedia_page.main: Major Guy Vernon Goodliffe  (17 September 1883 – 29 May 1963) was a career officer in the British Army and an English cricketer.  Goodliffe's batting and bowling styles are unknown.  He was born at Kensington, London and was educated at Charterhouse School.
